{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c0930754-7ae1-44d8-9d04-c8c5f81a734f","content":"`.testsettings` is a legacy format ignored by modern MSTest. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what your file configured and how to migrate each part:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout` property | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` |\n| Code coverage data collector | `<DataCollectionRunSettings>` |\n| `useLoadContext` assembly resolution | No longer needed in SDK-style projects |","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_lcbW1ScPaB5HdtRNvExuQC","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_coBlDU6wuWGTUArpANUPqN","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-dc07d99949d948d6a159d156f9effccf/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.CoverageCollectorDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral\" />\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-dc07d99949d948d6a159d156f9effccf/local.runsettings."},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_1oL4Vn5V2enRrEFwqBSrm5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-dc07d99949d948d6a159d156f9effccf/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>","new_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\local.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n  </PropertyGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-dc07d99949d948d6a159d156f9effccf/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"2ad81ede-8519-46fc-946a-e7958fab92a7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file with:\n1. Assembly resolution with `useLoadContext=\"true\"`\n2. Test timeout of 30000ms (30 seconds)\n3. Code coverage data collector\n\nThey've upgraded to MSTest 3.8.0. The `.testsettings` file is a legacy format that's no longer supported in modern MSTest. They need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file.\n\nLet me create the migration:\n\n1. **Test timeout** → `[Timeout]` attribute or `<TestRunParameters>` in `.runsettings`, or MSTest v3 supports `<Execution><TestTimeout>` in `.runsettings` under `<MSTest>`.\n\n\n2. **Code coverage** → Data collector in `.runsettings`\n3. **Assembly resolution / deployment** → In modern MSTest, deployment is handled differently. The `useLoadContext` is no longer needed.\n\nFor MSTest v3, I'm building the `.runsettings` file with the MSTest configuration section for timeouts and assembly resolution, along with the data collection settings for code coverage...","outputTokens":1124,"requestId":"0C0E:9A2B5:65A22B8:6EE1D06:69F01D3C"},"id":"352c13b0-38f8-4787-9343-cd0a04eefc2d","timestamp":"2026-04-28T02:37:01.360Z","parentId":"f55441cd-caa0-406c-9cb1-e34ba26e735f"}
